President Biden, Vice President Harris, and Secretary of Transportation Pete Buttigieg met with a bipartisan group of Members of Congress from the House Transportation and Infrastructure Committee to discuss the need to invest in American infrastructure. They discussed strengthening and enhancing roads, bridges, waterways, schools, housing, and more. The meeting focused on creating good-paying, union jobs, supporting economic recovery, and modernizing infrastructure to withstand climate change. The leaders emphasized the administration's commitment to creating skilled-trades jobs and positioning America for success in the 21st century. The meeting was seen as a constructive conversation to inform President Biden's plans for economic recovery.